# Monitor configuration template (PORTABLE EXAMPLE).
# This file is NOT used directly by Hyprland. install.sh copies it to
# ~/.config/hypr/monitors.conf on first install; edit that copy per machine.
# Source'd from hyprland.conf. Hyprland hot-reloads on `hyprctl keyword monitor "..."`.
# No semicolons; one rule per line; lowercase keys (matching repo style).

# ---- Per-machine setup (edit after install) ----
# Verify monitor names with `hyprctl monitors` and edit ~/.config/hypr/monitors.conf.
monitor=eDP-1,1920x1080@60,0x0,1

# Lid handling note (IMPORTANT):
#   hypridle has NO lid event support (verified vs upstream docs). It only
#   exposes idle-timeout listeners + D-Bus lock/sleep hooks. Toggling eDP-1
#   on lid close therefore CANNOT be done from hypridle.conf alone.
#
#   Recommended approach (needs a system file outside this repo):
#     /etc/systemd/logind.conf.d/lid.conf
#       [Login]
#       HandleLidSwitch=ignore
#       HandleLidSwitchExternalPower=ignore
#   Then let Hyprland/Hypridle disable eDP-1 via a udev rule, or run a small
#   acpid script that calls:
#       hyprctl keyword monitor "eDP-1,disable"        # lid close
#       hyprctl keyword monitor "eDP-1,1920x1080@60,0x0,1"  # lid open
#   See CHANGELOG/TODO: implement lid toggle as system-level drop-in.

# External monitor template (uncomment + edit after checking actual name with
# `hyprctl monitors`). Common names: HDMI-A-1, DP-1, DP-2.
#monitor=HDMI-A-1,2560x1440@60,0x0,1